criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  A clear diagnosis of lumbar spinal stenosis, and surgical level of L4-S1 (The levels
             to be operated on were decided by matching the clinical symptomatology with the
             radiological findings of the spinal levels that needed decompression);

          -  Patients have asymptomatic pre-existing spinal canal stenosis (cerebrospinal fluid
             occlusion grade=1) at adjacent segment.

          -  Failed at least eight weeks conservative treatment;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Unstable factors (slip, rotation, lateral bending, etc.) in adjacent segment L3/4;

          -  Preoperative sagittal and coronal imbalance of the spine;

          -  Lumbar infection and/or tumor diseases;

          -  A previous history of lumbar fusion surgery.
